images.name: Sam Darnold [600x400]
images.caption: Sam Darnold became the first quarterback in NFL history to win 14 regular-season games in consecutive seasons with different teams, having gone 14-3 in 2024 with the Vikings before doing the same with Seattle while making his second straight Pro Bowl.

articles.description: A victorious Seahawks locker room lauded their "unwavering" quarterback Sam Darnold, whose steadiness through injury- and turnover-related adversity this season culminated in a Super Bowl LX victory.
articles.headline: Seahawks laud 'unwavering' Sam Darnold after Super Bowl LX win

images.name: Drake Maye on SB loss: 'I'd like to go back to the beginning and redo it'
images.caption: Drake Maye talks to reporters about what he'd like to do over after the Patriots' Super Bowl loss to the Seahawks.

articles.description: Patriots QB Drake Maye acknowledged he received a pain-killing injection for his injured right throwing shoulder before Sunday's loss, but maintained he was "good to go" for the game and just didn't make enough plays in the end.
articles.headline: Patriots' Maye: Had injection for shoulder before Super Bowl

images.name: ESPN set to air Super Bowl LXI in 2027
images.caption: Scott Van Pelt takes "The Handoff" from Super Bowl LX as ESPN will air the Super Bowl in 2027 for the first time in network history.

articles.description: Scott Van Pelt takes "The Handoff" from Super Bowl LX as ESPN will air the Super Bowl in 2027 for the first time in network history.
articles.headline: ESPN set to air Super Bowl LXI in 2027

images.name: What does expected hiring of Klint Kubiak mean for Raiders?
images.caption: The "NFL Live" crew reacts to the Raiders being expected to hire Klint Kubiak as their next coach.

articles.description: Seahawks OC Klint Kubiak confirmed on NFL Network following the team's Super Bowl win over the Patriots on Sunday night that he will be leaving Seattle to take over as coach of the Raiders.
articles.headline: Klint Kubiak 'fired up' about taking Raiders' coaching job

images.name: Seattle Seahawks Super Bowl [608x342]

articles.description: The Seattle Seahawks beat the New England Patriots 29-13 in Super Bowl LX. Check out how the two teams stacked up against the other.
articles.headline: Seahawks-Patriots Super Bowl history: Records, stats, facts
